               <floruit notBefore="1685" notAfter="1707">He was a very loyal official of 
           
                  <persName ref="PRS5616IyasuI"> 
                     <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe </roleName> ʾIyāsu I</persName> in the course of twenty years period, 
                  <date>1685-1707</date>. 
                  <persName ref="PRS1954AnoreA">ʾAnore</persName> was successively governor of 
                  several territories under the control of the emperor. 
                  He was remarkable enough during the reign of   
                  <persName ref="PRS5616IyasuI">
                     <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName> ʾIyāsu I</persName>
                  insipte of the fact that he suffered some military setbacks. 
                  But following the death of the emperor, he was imprisoned in <placeName ref="LOC3577Gondar">Gondar</placeName>. 
                  </floruit>
               <death notBefore="1706" notAfter="1707"> He was executed somewhere near <placeName ref="LOC1022Abbay">ʾAbbāy</placeName> between December 1706 and January 1707.</death>
                  
                  
